method.description:
Adds a custom property info to a property. The dictionary must contain: name:[String](the property's name) and type:[int](see [code]TYPE_*[/code] in [@GlobalScope]), and optionally hint:[int](see [code]PROPERTY_HINT_*[/code] in [@GlobalScope]), hint_string:[String]. [b]Example:[/b] [codeblock] ProjectSettings.set("category/property_name", 0)
var property_info = { "name": "category/property_name", "type": TYPE_INT, "hint": PROPERTY_HINT_ENUM, "hint_string": "one,two,three" }
ProjectSettings.add_property_info(property_info) [/codeblock]
